[{"id":"VR857473","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows mirrors 1 and 2. Mirror 1 is oriented with the right edge tilted downward at an angle theta sub 0 from the horizontal and Mirror 2 is oriented horizontally directly below Mirror 1. A light beam originating from the bottom left of the figure travels slanted upwards to the right towards Mirror 1. The light beam is incident on Mirror 1 at the angle theta sub 0 relative to the normal to Mirror 1 shown as a dotted line. A note indicates the figure is not drawn to scale.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR857473.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two flat mirrors, Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, are located near each other, as shown in the figure. Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> is oriented at an angle <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub 0\"><math alttext=\"theta sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> from the horizontal, while Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> is oriented horizontally. A beam of light is incident on Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, making the same angle <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub 0\"><math alttext=\"theta sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> from the normal to the surface of the mirror. The beam reflects from Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> toward Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, and then reflects from Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>. Which of the following relations is true regarding the angles of <span class=\"formatted_text text_decoration:underline\">reflection</span> <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub 1\"><math alttext=\"theta sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span>and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub 2\"><math alttext=\"theta sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> as measured between the normal to each respective mirror's surface and the beam from mirrors <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, respectively?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR857473_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub 1 equals theta sub 2, which equals 0\"><math alttext=\"theta sub 1 equals theta sub 2, which equals 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choic